text: Coosa is an unincorporated community in Leake County, in the U.S. state of Mississippi. ==History== Coosa is a name most likely derived from the Choctaw language; it's purported to mean "reed brake". A post office called Coosa was established in 1879, and remained in operation until 1904. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Mississippi Category:Unincorporated communities in Leake County, Mississippi
title: Coosa, Mississippi
